  </div>

  <div class="comment-content">
    <div class="author"><div class="picture">
  <a href="/users/scarlett" title="View user profile."><img src="/sites/all/themes/newsflash/images/bagicon.png" alt="Scarlett&#039;s picture" title="Scarlett&#039;s picture"  /></a></div>
</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>Wrap your message under an Austrian label whenever you want, cherry-picked arguments may or may not go against reality.</p>
<p>Yes, the speed with which this is happening is downright scary. &nbsp;But what's happening is that a tiny fraction of the rich world economy is moving into bitcoin. &nbsp;A very tiny fraction is moving into something that has only 11,013,225 units, and this year will produce less units than citizens of San Diego. &nbsp;</p>
<p>Yes, there will be wild rides; yes, some fools will part with their money. &nbsp;</p>
<p>But bitcoin *will* reach--one day--a valuation of 10 Billion, and it will still be a tiny fraction of the world economy. &nbsp;That's what? Less than a week of Ben's weekly printer show.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

