    <p>Yes, except the lower withdrawal limits are on BITCOIN, not USD.</p>
<p>Mt.Gox has always had withdrawal limits. You have to get approved by providing increasing levels of ID to move increasing USD/BTC off the exchange.</p>
<p>This is nothing new, and the implication is the exact opposite of what you're implying. This is only for protection of exchange users in case their key/password is stolen. Never keep funds on the exchange for longer than it takes to close your trade.</p>
